{% block code_tab %}
    {% filter markdown %}
    ## Installation
    {% include "src/templates/partials/integration.njk" %}

    ## Attributes
    {% include "src/templates/partials/jsProps.njk" %}
    
    | Attribute             | Type    | Validation                                                                                    | Default | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |
    | --------------------- | ------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
    | `eds-aria-label`      | string  | --                                                                                            | --      | A string that will be set as the `aria-label` attribute on the container. This will also set `role="group"`.<br><br>Refer to the <eds-link eds-href="?tab=accessibility">Accessibility tab</eds-link> for more details.                                         |
    | `eds-aria-labelledby` | string  | --                                                                                            | --      | A string of `id`s separated by spaces that will be set as the `aria-labelledby` attribute on the container. This will also set `role="group"`.<br><br>Refer to the <eds-link eds-href="?tab=accessibility">Accessibility tab</eds-link> for more details.       |
    | `eds-dense`           | boolean | Anything other than an empty string, `true`, or `eds-dense` will be treated as `false`.       | `false` | Decreases the amount of vertical spacing between nexted Field Group components.                                                                                                                                                                                 |
    | `eds-fixed-width`     | boolean | Anything other than an empty string, `true`, or `eds-fixed-width` will be treated as `false`. | `false` | Allows the Field Group and its children to fill all available space. This value should be set to `true` if its children have a fixed width. (e.g., <eds-link eds-href="/components/input/input.html">Input</eds-link> component of type `ssn`)                  |
    | `eds-inline`          | string  | `never`, `at-512`, `at-768`, `at-960`, `at-1280`                                              | `never` | Determines the point at which items slotted within the Field Group go from stacked to inline.<br><br>For any breakpoint, if `eds-inline` is set to never, the content in the Field Group will stay stacked, while always will force the content to stay inline. |
    | `eds-vertical-align`  | string  | `top`, `center`, `bottom`                                                                     | `top`   | Determine how nested Field Groups are aligned vertically when `eds-inline` is used to display them an inline arrangement.                                                                                                                                       |

    ## Slots
    | Slot name     | Default content | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
    | ------------- | --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
    | `default`     | --              | Use this slot to group related <eds-link eds-href="/components/form/form.html">Form</eds-link> components, and/or display data content,  and apply appropriate vertical or horizontal spacing between them.<br><br>Additionally, Field Groups can be nested within one another to compose unique <eds-link eds-href="/components/form/form.html">Forms</eds-link> with multiple <eds-link eds-href="/components/form/form.html">Form</eds-link> controls.     |
    | `group-label` | --              | Use this slot to provide a <eds-link eds-href="/components/label/label.html">Label</eds-link> that applies to a group of related Field Group components.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |

    Refer to the <eds-link eds-href="/components/field-group/field-group.html?tab=examples">Examples tab</eds-link> for usage of the `default` slot.

    
    
    ## Events
    The Field Group component does not emit any custom events.

    ## Methods
    The Field Group component does not implement any public methods.

    ## CSS helper classes
    CSS helper classes provide common styles needed for slotted content. 

    | Class name                                         | Applies to | Outcome                                                                          |
    | -------------------------------------------------- | ---------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
    | `.eds-field-group__display-data`                   | `<p>`      | Applies the default styling to display data text.                                |
    | `.eds-field-group__display-data--small`            | `<p>`      | Applies the responsive font-size and line-height attributes for small text.      |
    | `.eds-field-group__display-data--large`            | `<p>`      | Applies the responsive font-size and line-height attributes for large text.      |
    | `.eds-field-group__display-data--performance-gain` | `<p>`      | Applies the color attribute for indicating a performance gain.                   |
    | `.eds-field-group__display-data--performance-loss` | `<p>`      | Applies the color attribute for indicating a performance loss.                   |


    ## CSS modifier classes
    {% include "src/templates/partials/cssModifiers.njk" %}

    | Class name                                | Applies to              | Outcome                                                                                                                  |
    | ----------------------------------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
    | `.eds-field-group--standard`              | `.eds-field-group-root` | Applies the standard amount of spacing between nested Field Groups                                                       |
    | `.eds-field-group--dense`                 | `.eds-field-group-root` | Applies a dense amount of vertical spacing between nested Field Groups                                                   |
    | `.eds-field-group--fixed-width`           | `.eds-field-group-root` | Prevents the Field Group from growing horizontally to fill its container.                                                |
    | `.eds-field-group--inline-always`         | `.eds-field-group-root` | Nested Field Groups will be arranged horizontally and will never stack.                                                  |
    | `.eds-field-group--inline-at-512`         | `.eds-field-group-root` | Nested Field Groups will be arranged horizontally at a screen width of 512px and above, otherwise they will be stacked.  |
    | `.eds-field-group--inline-at-768`         | `.eds-field-group-root` | Nested Field Groups will be arranged horizontally at a screen width of 768px and above, otherwise they will be stacked.  |
