    ## Group labels
    - There is often a desire to <eds-link eds-href="/components/label/label.html">Label</eds-link> a group of related form controls. For example, when collecting a user’s date of birth, each individual form control may be labeled as "Month", "Day", or "Year" but the entire group is labeled as "Date of birth".  

    - In order to build a <eds-link eds-href="/components/form/form.html">Form</eds-link> that is accessible to all users, you must slot a <eds-link eds-href="/components/label/label.html">Label</eds-link> using the `group-label` slot and you must use the `eds-aria-label` or `eds-aria-labelledby` attribute in order to associate the group label with the group of related form controls. The value of `eds-aria-labelledby` is the `id` of the associated <eds-link eds-href="/components/label/label.html">Label</eds-link>.

    - `eds-aria-label` should only be used if the group has no visible <eds-link eds-href="/components/label/label.html">Label</eds-link>;
    otherwise, it is recommended to use `eds-aria-labelledby` to associate the
    visible <eds-link eds-href="/components/label/label.html">Label</eds-link> with the group. By providing a value to `eds-aria-label` or
    `eds-aria-labelledby`, `role="group"` will be automatically added.

